cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with pedestrian detection in street scenes using visual attention mechanisms. Additionally, the paper proposes a local statistical multichannel descriptor to incorporate both color and gradient information, which is a common technique used in computer vision. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as feature selection and classification, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. 

Furthermore, the paper proposes a multidirection and multiscale contrast scheme based on grid cells, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
